{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "648b5a65417cc3fb48d66327", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 3, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 180, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "EM", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba2"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "648b5a3a0d9d0b909f7b648a", "title": "JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr)", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "<p>A particle is oscillating on the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis with an amplitude <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math> about the point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>cm</mi></math> with a frequency. A concave mirror of focal length <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math> is placed at the origin (see figure).</p><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/ce281efe-8aa9-40d6-a4f0-6187b0bdb05a-image.png\" style=\"width: 290px; height: 149px;\" /><br />Identify the correct statements?<br />(i) The image executes periodic motion.<br />(ii) The image executes non-periodic motion.<br />(iii) The turning points of the image are asymmetric with respect to the image of the point at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>X</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>cm</mi></math>.<br />(iv) The distance between the turning points of the oscillation of the image is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>100</mn><mn>21</mn></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi>cm</mi></math>.</p>", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "GfskL", "text": "(ii, iii)", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "pAxne", "text": "(i, iii, iv)", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "e8Yka", "text": "(i, iv)", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "iboEZ", "text": "(ii, iv)", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p>Recall the proper formula of mirror formula,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>f</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>v</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>u</mi></mfrac></math>, given&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>&nbsp;then the formula of the concave mirror,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>v</mi></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>. As,&nbsp;image copies the time period of the object&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi>A</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;is right as well. It will be a periodic motion. For one extreme,&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>v</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>40</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>, right arrow.</p><p>For other extreme,&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>12</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>v</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>60</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>. These points are asymmetrical about&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>.&nbsp;Now amplitude of oscillation of image,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mn>40</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>60</mn><mn>7</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>100</mn><mn>21</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ78565487", "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "bucket": "", "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["61964c922db938c3ec5c87e8", "6160243a86b518ff2afd9379", "6160243ae896b71d7f0f03d9", "61bb820fc1f688a120dfda9f", "61964c9102fe1de035852896", "61e7bd71a2dd607688d6c01b", "61c08989e3eba41a9e71354b", "61602437a04b762ba7dfcb47", "61602438690b07c861db4cc9", "6160243b7384a30f11cacc9e", "629109ef0299d67104ca49d5", "629f3a9295d059d5cc4d982e", "629621243e04d5d8ca7b92bd", "629f390e4eb9140dc965900d", "64eb06dd3118f713ecfef1b0", "66d5853ba75f05ee8564f575", "67921d651d5b5072da5e9aae", "67fdff46378e1624ea7b6984", "680920293a10446a207fdecb"], "cpyqbExams": ["615f0e999476412f48314daf", "616059af0283de43c87e3e23"]}}